'''Fidel Escobar Mendieta''' (born 9 January 1995) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Liga FPD]] club [[Deportivo Saprissa|Saprissa]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
===San Francisco===
Born in [[Panama City]], Escobar graduated from [[San Francisco F.C.|San Francisco]]'s youth setup, and made his senior debut during the 2012–13 campaign, aged only 18. During the next season he established himself as a first team regular making 14 starts and scoring one goal. On 26 October 2013, Escobar scored his first goal for ''Los Monjes'' in a 2–0 victory over [[Chorrillo F.C.|Chorrillo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chepo y San Francisco creen en las semifinales
|url=http://lpf.com.pa/w/chepo-y-san-francisco-creen-en-las-semifinales/|website=lpf.com.pa|access-date=27 October 2013|language=es}}</ref>

===Sporting San Miguelito===
After impressing with San Francisco, Escobar was signed by [[Sporting San Miguelito]] for the 2014 Clausura season. He made 14 appearances scoring one goal in his first season at the club. On 16 March 2014, Escobar scored his first goal with San Miguelito in a 2–2 draw with [[Alianza F.C. (Panama)|Alianza]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chorrillo es líder tras 11 jornadas completas
|url=http://lpf.com.pa/w/chorrillo-es-lider-tras-11-jornadas-completas/|website=lpf.com.pa|access-date=14 March 2014|language=es}}</ref> In his two and a half seasons with the club Escobar made 65 league appearances scoring six goals.

====Sporting B (loan)====
As a result of his impressive play with his club and at the Under-20 World Cup Escobar received the attention of European clubs. During July 2016, Escobar was sent on loan with an option to buy to [[Sporting Clube de Portugal]]'s reserve side [[Sporting CP B|Sporting B]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sporting: Fidel Escobar está a caminho de Lisboa
|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga/05-07-2016/sporting-fidel-escobar-esta-a-caminho-de-lisboa|website=maisfutebol.iol.pt|access-date=5 July 2016|language=pt}}</ref> Escobar made his debut for Sporting B on 6 August 2016 playing the entire match in a 1–2 loss to [[Portimonense S.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|title=SPORTING B-PORTIMONENSE, 1-2: PIRES BISA NA REVIRAVOLTA ALGARVIA
|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/sporting-b-portimonense-1-2-pires-bisa-na-reviravolta-algarvia.html|website=record.pt|access-date=6 August 2016|language=pt}}</ref> In January 2017, Escobar attempted to terminate his contract with Sporting in search of other opportunities and was threatened with legal action by the Portuguese side.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sporting: Fidel no quiere volver a Lisboa|url=http://futbolcentroamerica.com/5762/fidel-escobar-no-quiere-regresar-a-sporting-de-lisboa-y-pide-rescindir|website=futbolcentroamerica.com|access-date=12 January 2017|language=es|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906232117/http://futbolcentroamerica.com/5762/fidel-escobar-no-quiere-regresar-a-sporting-de-lisboa-y-pide-rescindir|archive-date=6 September 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Escobar eventually apologized to the club and was reinstated for the second half of the season. He made his return to the side on 15 April 2017, starting in a 2–0 victory over [[União da Madeira]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SPORTING B-UNIÃO DA MADEIRA, 2-0: LEÕES REGRESSAM ÀS VITÓRIAS
|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/sporting-b-uniao-da-madeira-2-0-leoes-regressam-as-vitorias.html|website=record.pt|access-date=15 April 2017|language=pt}}</ref>

====New York Red Bulls (loan)====
On 27 July 2017 it was announced that Escobar was joining [[New York Red Bulls]] on an 18-month loan.<ref>{{cite web|title=New York Red Bulls Add Panama International Fidel Escobar on Loan
|url=https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2017/07/27/new-york-red-bulls-add-panama-international-fidel-escobar-loan|website=newyorkredbulls.com|access-date=27 July 2017}}</ref> For his play on 10 March 2018, in which he helped lead New York to a 4–0 victory over [[Portland Timbers]] in the team's first league match of the season, Escobar was named to the Starting XI for Major League Soccer's Team of the Week.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fidel Escobar in Starting XI for Team of the Week presented by Audi|url=https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2018/03/12/fidel-escobar-starting-xi-team-week-presented-audi-sean-davis-carlos-rivas-bench|website=newyorkredbulls.com|access-date=12 March 2018|archive-date=13 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313095326/https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2018/03/12/fidel-escobar-starting-xi-team-week-presented-audi-sean-davis-carlos-rivas-bench|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Escobar was loaned to affiliate side [[New York Red Bulls II]] of the [[United Soccer League]] for the match against [[Tampa Bay Rowdies]] on 14 April 2018. He opened the scoring for New York in the 5–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|title=Red Bulls II Romp Past Rowdies|url=https://www.uslsoccer.com/news_article/show/907855?referrer_id=2424350|website=uslsoccer.com|date = 14 April 2018|access-date=14 April 2018}}</ref>

Escobar's loan was not extended by the Red Bulls at the end of their 2018 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorkredbulls.com/post/2018/12/04/new-york-red-bulls-announce-end-season-roster-updates|title=New York Red Bulls Announce End of Season Roster Updates|work=NewYorkRedBulls.com}}</ref>

====Córdoba (loan)====
On 10 July 2019, after a six-month spell at [[Correcaminos UAT]], Escobar joined Spanish [[Segunda División B]] side [[Córdoba CF]] on loan for one year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cordobacf.com/noticia/fidel-escobar-tercer-fichaje-del-cordoba-cf|title=Fidel Escobar, tercer fichaje del Córdoba CF|trans-title=Fidel Escobar, third signing of Córdoba CF|publisher=Córdoba CF|language=es|date=10 July 2019|access-date=16 August 2019}}</ref>

===Alcorcón===
On 28 July 2020, Escobar agreed to a three-year contract with [[AD Alcorcón]] in [[Segunda División]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adalcorcon.com/noticia/fidel-escobar-primer-fichaje-de-la-a-d-alcorcon-2020-2021|title=Fidel Escobar, primer fichaje de la A.D. Alcorcón 2020–2021|trans-title=Fidel Escobar, first signing of A.D. Alcorcón 2020–2021|publisher=AD Alcorcón|language=es|date=28 July 2020|access-date=9 August 2020}}</ref> On 31 January 2022, he was loaned to [[Primera División RFEF]] side [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.adalcorcon.com/noticia/salidas-de-futbolistas-de-la-primera-plantilla-alfarera|title=Salidas de futbolistas de la primera plantilla alfarera|trans-title=Departure of footballers from the first team ''alfarero''|publisher=AD Alcorcón|language=es|date=31 January 2022|accessdate=1 February 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
Escobar played at the [[2015 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{FIFA player|385030}}</ref> He made his debut in the competition on 30 May 2015 scoring an 84th-minute equalizer in a 2–2 draw against heavily favored side [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Argentina empató con Panamá en el debut del Mundial Sub-20|url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/1797351-argentina-empato-con-panama-en-el-debut-del-mundial-sub-20|website=lanacion.com.ar|date=30 May 2015|access-date=30 May 2015|language=es|archive-date=11 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011182638/https://www.lanacion.com.ar/1797351-argentina-empato-con-panama-en-el-debut-del-mundial-sub-20|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Escobar made his senior debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] in a February 2015 [[friendly match]] against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]].

In May 2018 he was named in Panama's preliminary 35 man [[Panama national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia, and played all three matches in an eventual group-stage exit.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists {{!}} Goal.com|access-date=5 June 2018}}</ref>

